declarations.name: loadPrimer
declarations.description: Main function to load the Primer SDK with all required dependencies and styles

PrimerCheckoutComponent implements the main checkout experience.
This component includes a CSS-only loader that displays before the JavaScript
is fully loaded, ensuring users see a loading indicator immediately.

The loader can be disabled by:
1. Adding the 'loader-disabled' attribute to the component
2. Setting the CSS custom property --primer-loader-disabled: 1

Controller that handles processing and application of custom styles to Lit components.
Safely converts JSON style objects to CSS variables applied to the host element.

parameters.name: jsonString
parameters.description: The JSON string representing custom styles.

members.description:
Processes the customStyles JSON string.
Expected JSON contains only CSS variable properties in camelCase.

parameters.name: property
parameters.description: The CSS property name to validate.

members.description: Validates a CSS property name to ensure it follows expected patterns.

members.name: isValidCssValue
members.description:
Validates a CSS value to ensure it only contains safe, expected characters.
Allowed characters include alphanumerics, whitespace, and common CSS punctuation.
This helps prevent CSS injection attacks.

members.name: getCssVarName
members.description:
Gets the CSS variable name for a camelCase property key.
Uses caching for performance.

members.name: applyStyles

parameters.name: styles
parameters.description: An object with style keys and corresponding CSS values.

members.description:
Transforms a styles object into CSS variables and applies them to the host element.
Each key (in camelCase) is converted into a kebab-case CSS variable prefixed with '--'.
Only valid CSS properties and values are applied.

parameters.name: key

members.description: Removes all custom styles from the host element

so that merchant CSS can override our default theme variables.
